he loop infrastructure. `executor-config` parses per-iteration executor settings from a shared schema so every consumer calls the same executor shape. `executor-audit` appends a provenance block to each iteration JSONL so you can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration. `prompt-pack` renders the iteration prompt template. `post-dispatch-validate` checks that an iteration produced valid markdown, JSONL and delta outputs before the state log accepts them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` implements permission-scope checks for tool calls but has zero production callers today — built and unit-tested, not wired into any dispatch path. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:\n  Line 25: | `executor-audit.ts` | Executor provenance and dispatch failure JSONL records. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md:\n  Line 750: Non-native executor runs append an `executor` block with model and runtime settings to the iteration's JSONL record via `executor-audit.ts`. Native runs are recoverable from YAML alone.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/receipt-crypto.ts:\n  Line 10: // (executor-audit.ts) and is never imported or referenced here. Keeping the key\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:\n  Line 134: > **Feature File:** [DLR-002](../manual-testing-playbook/executor/executor-audit.md)\n\n  Line 852: | Executor | `tests/unit/executor-config.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/executor-audit*.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/cli-matrix.vitest.ts` | Executor parsing, audit, fallback, and CLI dispatch behavior. |\n\n  Line 870: | DLR-002 | [F002 Executor audit](../feature-catalog/executor/executor-audit.md) | [executor/executor-audit.md](../manual-testing-playbook/executor/executor-audit.md) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/changelog/v1.7.0.0.md:\n  Line 1: This release mirrors `deep-research` v1.10.0.0 hardening across the review loop. Executor identity is written on the first JSONL record of every non-native review iteration. A new `dispatch_failure` event preserves executor attribution across crashes and timeouts. Copilot large-prompt handling gains `@path` fallback in both review YAML dispatch branches. The shared `executor-audit.ts`, `post-dispatch-validate.ts`, `description-repair.ts` and `timestamp-normalize.ts` modules are consumed unchanged. The readiness contract in SKILL.md narrows to the four trust-state values the seven code-graph handlers actually emit. The retry-budget 