{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784620479428,"sessionID":"ses_07c62e1e5ffemFsnADH4fVqMT5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ODgWymNwC8KcUYF6F3ZfQg3X","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Research Strategy: Styles Naming and Manifest Consolidation\"\n3: description: \"Detached five-iteration research strategy for kebab-case migration and single-manifest design.\"\n4: importance_tier: important\n5: contextType: research\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Deep Research Strategy: Styles Naming and Manifest Consolidation\n9: \n10: ## 1. RESEARCH TOPIC\n11: \n12: Bring the styles backend into kebab-case conformance, produce an exact and safe rename/reference migration, and consolidate the crawl and retrieval manifests into one source of truth.\n13: \n14: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n15: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n16: [None yet]\n17: \n18: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n19: \n20: ## 3. NON-GOALS\n21: \n22: - Do not execute renames or change the researched styles backend.\n23: - Do not decide whether SQLite becomes the default retrieval path; that belongs to the adjacent DB-fate packet.\n24: - Do not restructure the 1,290 style directories beyond what is needed to explain manifest ownership and path effects.\n25: \n26: ## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n27: \n28: - Complete exactly five evidence-bearing iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n29: - Produce an exact rename map, a reference-update/cutover plan, and one manifest consolidation design grounded in repository evidence.\n30: - Preserve unresolved contradictions and implementation dependencies explicitly rather than inventing certainty.\n31: \n32: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n33: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n34: [None yet]\n35: \n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n37: \n38: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n39: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n40: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n41: - exact-token searches anchored in the naming canon separated filesystem paths from unrelated underscore identifiers and exposed the dependency closure by responsibility. (iteration 1)\n42: \n43: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n44: \n45: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n46: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n47: - the first repository-wide bare-token search was noisy because `_db` and `_engine` are valid code identifiers outside this naming scope. (iteration 1)\n48: \n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n50: \n51: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n52: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n53: ### Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n54: - What was tried: Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4]\n55: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n56: - Do NOT retry: Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4]\n57: \n58: ### Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n59: - What was tried: Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n60: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n61: - Do NOT retry: Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n62: \n63: ### Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n64: - What was tried: Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries]\n65: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n66: - Do NOT retry: Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries]\n67: \n68: ### No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n69: - What was tried: No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive.\n70: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n71: - Do NOT retry: No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive.\n72: \n73: ### The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n74: - What was tried: The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope]\n75: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n76: - Do NOT retry: The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope]\n77: \n78: ### Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n79: - What was tried: Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34]\n80: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n81: - Do NOT retry: Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34]\n82: \n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n84: \n85: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n86: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n87: - Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4] (iteration 1)\n88: - Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56] (iteration 1)\n89: - Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries] (iteration 1)\n90: - No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive. (iteration 1)\n91: - The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope] (iteration 1)\n92: - Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34] (iteration 1)\n93: \n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n95: \n96: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n97: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n98: - Completed pivots: 0\n99: - Failed pivots: 0\n100: - Audited overrides: 0\n101: - Saturated: none yet\n102: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n103: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n104: \n105: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n106: \n107: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n108: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n109: - Confirm indirect/runtime-computed path construction and the exact baseline/post-cutover validation command set. (iteration 1)\n110: - Decide which data is canonical versus derived, and specify hash/provenance/deterministic-regeneration semantics. (iteration 1)\n111: - Define rollback and cutover proof for both naming and later consolidation, including stale generated artifacts. (iteration 1)\n112: - Map every field, invariant, and lifecycle role in both manifest schemas, including writer ownership and ordering guarantees. (iteration 1)\n113: \n114: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n115: \n116: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n117: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n118: [All tracked questions are resolved]\n119: \n120: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n121: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n122: \n123: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n124: \n125: - The packet spec confirms `_db`, `_engine`, `_harness`, `_manifest.json`, and `_retrieval-manifest.json` are in scope and implementation is excluded. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/spec.md:50]\n126: - The parent gap analysis identifies both manifests as listing 1,290 styles but serving crawl and DB-generation roles with different schemas. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:44]\n127: - Focused memory retrieval returned the active packet spec and no additional canonical decision record. [SOURCE: memory:sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests]\n128: - `resource-map.md` is absent from the packet; the coverage gate is skipped.\n129: \n130: ## 14. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n131: \n132: - Max iterations: 5\n133: - Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before the hard iteration cap\n134: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n135: - Artifact root: detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n136: - Reducer controls machine-owned sections; leaf iterations write only their narrative, state append, and delta.\n\n(End of file - total 136 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Research Strategy: Styles Naming and Manifest Consolidation\"\ndescription: \"Detached five-iteration research strategy for kebab-case migration and single-manifest design.\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: research\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy: Styles Naming and Manifest Consolidation\n\n## 1. RESEARCH TOPIC\n\nBring the styles backend into kebab-case conformance, produce an exact and safe rename/reference migration, and consolidate the crawl and retrieval manifests into one source of truth.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n[None yet]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Research Strategy: Styles Naming and Manifest Consolidation\"\ndescription: \"Detached five-iteration research strategy for kebab-case migration and single-manifest design.\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: research\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy: Styles Naming and Manifest Consolidation\n\n## 1. RESEARCH TOPIC\n\nBring the styles backend into kebab-case conformance, produce an exact and safe rename/reference migration, and consolidate the crawl and retrieval manifests into one source of truth.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n[None yet]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not execute renames or change the researched styles backend.\n- Do not decide whether SQLite becomes the default retrieval path; that belongs to the adjacent DB-fate packet.\n- Do not restructure the 1,290 style directories beyond what is needed to explain manifest ownership and path effects.\n\n## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- Complete exactly five evidence-bearing iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n- Produce an exact rename map, a reference-update/cutover plan, and one manifest consolidation design grounded in repository evidence.\n- Preserve unresolved contradictions and implementation dependencies explicitly rather than inventing certainty.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n- exact-token searches anchored in the naming canon separated filesystem paths from unrelated underscore identifiers and exposed the dependency closure by responsibility. (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n- the first repository-wide bare-token search was noisy because `_db` and `_engine` are valid code identifiers outside this naming scope. (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n### Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4]\n\n### Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n\n### Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries]\n\n### No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive.\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive.\n\n### The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope]\n\n### Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- Assuming the retrieval manifest is canonical because it is richer: its `crawlManifestHash` explicitly signals derivation from crawl state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:4] (iteration 1)\n- Blindly rewriting changelogs and completed spec history: the canon requires those surfaces to retain historical names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56] (iteration 1)\n- Combining naming moves and manifest-schema consolidation into one cutover: doing so would remove the name-only parity boundary and make regressions harder to attribute. [INFERENCE: two independent change dimensions require separate verification boundaries] (iteration 1)\n- No exhausted approach should be promoted after this first pass; the narrowed exact-path search was productive. (iteration 1)\n- The initial repository-wide search for bare `_db`, `_engine`, and `_harness` produced unrelated identifiers outside `sk-design`; narrowing to filesystem-shaped tokens and the owning skill removed that noise. [INFERENCE: bare underscore identifiers are code identifiers outside the filesystem-naming scope] (iteration 1)\n- Treating leading-underscore backend paths as exempt: they are authored JavaScript/JSON filesystem names, not Python packages, tool-mandated names, generated output names, or frozen history. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34] (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n- Confirm indirect/runtime-computed path construction and the exact baseline/post-cutover validation command set. (iteration 1)\n- Decide which data is canonical versus derived, and specify hash/provenance/deterministic-regeneration semantics. (iteration 1)\n- Define rollback and cutover proof for both naming and later consolidation, including stale generated artifacts. (iteration 1)\n- Map every field, invariant, and lifecycle role in both manifest schemas, including writer ownership and ordering guarantees. (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[All tracked questions are resolved]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- The packet spec confirms `_db`, `_engine`, `_harness`, `_manifest.json`, and `_retrieval-manifest.json` are in scope and implementation is excluded. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/spec.md:50]\n- The parent gap analysis identifies both manifests as listing 1,290 styles but serving crawl and DB-generation roles with different schemas. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:44]\n- Focused memory retrieval returned the active packet spec and no additional canonical decision record. [SOURCE: memory:sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests]\n- `resource-map.md` is absent from the packet; the coverage gate is skipped.\n\n## 14. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before the hard iteration cap\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Artifact root: detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n- Reducer controls machine-owned sections; leaf iterations write only their narrative, state append, and delta.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":136,"totalLines":136,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784620479420,"end":1784620479427}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09fc7543aeb4a2d6016a5f25bf4c388191af210d73ed4cd7bd"}},"id":"prt_f83ab737a00126qkOVl7mYUu2u","sessionID":"ses_07c62e1e5ffemFsnADH4fVqMT5","messageID":"msg_f83ab24f4001ZTedrzidqQFUlm"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784620479507,"sessionID":"ses_07c62e1e5ffemFsnADH4fVqMT5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_34HH8BGDW7U17IZanHhcCZDS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","limit":400},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784619539276-ffno9q\",\n3:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n4:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n5:   \"generation\": 1,\n6:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n7:   \"terminalStop\": null,\n8:   \"keyQuestions\": [],\n9:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n10:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n11:   \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [\n12:     {\n13:       \"text\": \"Confirm indirect/runtime-computed path construction and the exact baseline/post-cutover validation command set.\",\n14:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n15:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n16:     },\n17:     {\n18:       \"text\": \"Decide which data is canonical versus derived, and specify hash/provenance/deterministic-regeneration semantics.\",\n19:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n20:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n21:     },\n22:     {\n23:       \"text\": \"Define rollback and cutover proof for both naming and later consolidation, including stale generated artifacts.\",\n24:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n25:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n26:     },\n27:     {\n28:       \"text\": \"Map every field, invariant, and lifecycle role in both manifest schemas, including writer ownership and ordering guarantees.\",\n29:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n30:       \"source\": \"iteration-markdown\"\n31:     }\n32:   ],\n33:   \"uncoveredQuestions\": [],\n34:   \"keyFindings\": [\n35:     {\n36:       \"id\": \"finding-1-2-exact-rename-map-the-dependency-closure-rename-is\",\n37:       \"text\": \"**Exact rename map.** The dependency-closure rename is:\",\n38:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n39:       \"sources\": [\n40:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n41:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n42:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10`\",\n43:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-100`\",\n44:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:30-32`\",\n45:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:36-172`\",\n46:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:44`\",\n47:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:649`\",\n48:         \"Exact-reference Grep/`rg --count-matches` inventory across `.opencode/skills/sk-design`\"\n49:       ]\n50:     },\n51:     {\n52:       \"id\": \"finding-1-3-exhaustive-live-surface-direct-reference-inventory-140-occurrences-in-46-files-t\",\n53:       \"text\": \"**Exhaustive live-surface direct-reference inventory: 140 occurrences in 46 files.** The files are grouped by migration responsibility; every listed mutable reference must be updated in the same dependency-closure cutover unless explicitly identified as frozen history. [INFERENCE: repository-scoped exact-token inventory, grouped from `rg --count-matches` output]\",\n54:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n55:       \"sources\": [\n56:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n57:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n58:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10`\",\n59:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-100`\",\n60:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:30-32`\",\n61:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:36-172`\",\n62:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:44`\",\n63:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:649`\",\n64:         \"Exact-reference Grep/`rg --count-matches` inventory across `.opencode/skills/sk-design`\"\n65:       ]\n66:     },\n67:     {\n68:       \"id\": \"finding-1-1-naming-authority-and-exemption-result-the-canon-states-that-directory-names-and-\",\n69:       \"text\": \"**Naming authority and exemption result.** The canon states that directory names and filenames use kebab-case; exemptions cover Python source/package names, generated/tool-mandated names, runner magic, vendored trees, and frozen history. The three JavaScript backend directories and two authored JSON manifests match none of those exemptions. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:34]\",\n70:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n71:       \"sources\": [\n72:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n73:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n74:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10`\",\n75:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-100`\",\n76:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:30-32`\",\n77:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:36-172`\",\n78:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:44`\",\n79:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:649`\",\n80:         \"Exact-reference Grep/`rg --count-matches` inventory across `.opencode/skills/sk-design`\"\n81:       ]\n82:     },\n83:     {\n84:       \"id\": \"finding-1-20-repository-wide-references-need-scope-classification-not-blind-replacement-activ\",\n85:       \"text\": \"**Repository-wide references need scope classification, not blind replacement.** Active external consumers such as the styles Rust-opportunity packet point at `_db/retrieval.mjs`, but completed spec history is explicitly frozen; those paths should be recorded as historical rather than rewritten. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/spec.md:19] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\",\n86:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n87:       \"sources\": [\n88:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n89:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n90:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10`\",\n91:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-100`\",\n92:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:30-32`\",\n93:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:36-172`\",\n94:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:44`\",\n95:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:649`\",\n96:         \"Exact-reference Grep/`rg --count-matches` inventory across `.opencode/skills/sk-design`\"\n97:       ]\n98:     },\n99:     {\n100:       \"id\": \"finding-1-21-safe-rename-sequence-capture-a-baseline-on-all-current-engine-database-mode-corp\",\n101:       \"text\": \"**Safe rename sequence.** Capture a baseline on all current engine/database/mode-corpus tests; perform all five moves and all mutable references as one dependency-closure change; update cross-directory imports and runtime path constants first, then fixtures/tests, scripts, and mutable docs; run the same complete gates; only after name-only parity should manifest consolidation change schema or remove a file. Do not leave compatibility symlinks or duplicate manifests after the atomic cutover, because coordinated consumers are fully inventoried. [INFERENCE: the direct-reference closure above makes a single atomic cutover smaller and safer than prolonged dual paths, while a separate schema phase isolates behavioral failures]\",\n102:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n103:       \"sources\": [\n104:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n105:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n106:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10`\",\n107:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-100`\",\n108:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:30-32`\",\n109:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:36-172`\",\n110:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:44`\",\n111:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:649`\",\n112:         \"Exact-reference Grep/`rg --count-matches` inventory across `.opencode/skills/sk-design`\"\n113:       ]\n114:     },\n115:     {\n116:       \"id\": \"finding-1-22-the-manifests-overlap-in-membership-but-are-not-schema-equivalent-the-crawl-file\",\n117:       \"text\": \"**The manifests overlap in membership but are not schema-equivalent.** The crawl file is a top-level array of capture lifecycle records (`uuid`, source URL/time, slug, capture status/time, error); the retrieval file is a versioned generation object with `generationHash`, `crawlManifestHash`, `recordCount`, and enriched searchable `styles` records. The retrieval schema already declares its derivation relationship through `crawlManifestHash`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:3] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:3]\",\n118:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n119:       \"sources\": [\n120:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n121:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n122:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10`\",\n123:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-100`\",\n124:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:30-32`\",\n125:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:36-172`\",\n126:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:44`\",\n127:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:649`\",\n128:         \"Exact-reference Grep/`rg --count-matches` inventory across `.opencode/skills/sk-design`\"\n129:       ]\n130:     },\n131:     {\n132:       \"id\": \"finding-1-23-this-iteration-does-not-choose-the-canonical-manifest-renaming-both-files-is-mec\",\n133:       \"text\": \"**This iteration does not choose the canonical manifest.** Renaming both files is mechanically resolved, but choosing one physical source of truth requires tracing generation code, hash construction, writer ownership, invalidation behavior, and deterministic regeneration. Treating the richer retrieval manifest as automatically canonical would invert its current declared dependency on the crawl hash. [INFERENCE: `_retrieval-manifest.json` includes `crawlManifestHash`, so canonicality cannot be inferred from schema richness alone]\",\n134:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n135:       \"sources\": [\n136:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n137:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n138:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10`\",\n139:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-100`\",\n140:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:30-32`\",\n141:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:36-172`\",\n142:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:44`\",\n143:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:649`\",\n144:         \"Exact-reference Grep/`rg --count-matches` inventory across `.opencode/skills/sk-design`\"\n145:       ]\n146:     },\n147:     {\n148:       \"id\": \"finding-1-19-changelog-v1-6-0-0-md-records-the-paths-as-shipped-and-remains-unchanged-under-t\",\n149:       \"text\": \"`changelog/v1.6.0.0.md` records the paths as shipped and remains unchanged under the canon's frozen-history exception. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\",\n150:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n151:       \"sources\": [\n152:         \"`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:18-88`\",\n153:         \"`.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-105`\",\n154:   