{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784621825337,"sessionID":"ses_07c62e1e5ffemFsnADH4fVqMT5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bZyxtZS7eFPH9NPDnGuoUMbE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-004.md","limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-004.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 4: Executable Cutover Validation, Rollback, and Indirect Consumers\n2: \n3: ## Focus\n4: \n5: Convert the established name map and canonical-manifest architecture into an executable, two-checkpoint migration plan. This pass identifies runtime-computed paths, confirms the commands that repository package files and mode READMEs actually expose, separates inferred styles-backend commands from confirmed commands, and defines proof and rollback obligations for the name-only cutover and the later v1-to-v2 consolidation.\n6: \n7: ## Actions Taken\n8: \n9: 1. Read the detached config, state, strategy, registry, and iterations 1-3; confirmed run 4, `progressiveSynthesis=false`, lineage-only writes, two remaining key questions, and the prohibition on combining naming and schema changes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-config.json:16-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:15-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:83-86]\n10: 2. Searched the live `sk-design` surface for direct legacy tokens and runtime path construction (`import.meta.url`, `path.resolve`, `path.join`, and `new URL`) to distinguish static imports from computed consumers. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68]\n11: 3. Located package manifests and executable test documentation. Only `design-md-generator/backend/package.json` exists under `sk-design`; it defines `typecheck`, `build`, and `test`, while the four mode-corpus READMEs expose direct `node --test` commands. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32]\n12: 4. Reconciled the command/path evidence with prior writer, projector, stale-cache, database-generation, and frozen-history findings to derive exact ordering, checkpoint boundaries, and deletion criteria without running implementation or mutating tests. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:685-782] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:623-853] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n13: \n14: ## Findings\n15: \n16: 1. **The indirect consumer closure adds computed paths, fixture joins, and generated TypeScript output to the direct-reference inventory.** `study-prepare.ts` computes both the style-library CLI and retrieval-manifest locations with `path.resolve`, so changing imports alone would leave its runtime path stale. Mode-corpus fixtures construct `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` with `path.join`, so those strings must change even when their source imports resolve after the directory move. The backend build compiles TypeScript to `dist`; source is authoritative, then `npm run build` regenerates output, and generated output must not be hand-edited. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:14-20]\n17: \n18: 2. **The executable baseline is a command matrix, not one package-level test command.** Repository-confirmed commands are `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`, and `npm test` from `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/`, plus `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, and `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs` from the repository root. No styles-level `package.json` was found, so `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/*.test.mjs` and the corresponding `_db` command are **inferred commands**, not repository-declared scripts; implementation must either confirm them by successful baseline execution or add an explicit documented runner before relying on them as gates. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32] [INFERENCE: the only package manifest found under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/**/package.json` is the backend package, while engine/database `.test.mjs` files are inventoried in iteration 1]\n19: \n20: 3. **Checkpoint A is an atomic name-only dependency-closure cutover.** First record baseline command exits and stable observable fixtures: byte hashes and counts for both current manifests, representative legacy query/hydration results, database status/current-generation pointer, and the exact legacy-token inventory. Then move all five paths; update runtime imports and manifest constants first, computed `path.resolve`/`path.join` consumers second, test fixtures third, source scripts and generated-output inputs fourth, and mutable docs/operator commands last. Run the identical command matrix, require old/new manifest bytes to match across renamed paths, require retrieval/query/hydration and DB status snapshots to match, and require a scoped search to find no legacy tokens outside frozen history. Rollback A is one reversal of the five moves plus the same reference patch; schema and hash behavior remain untouched, so any behavioral delta is a naming regression. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:73-177] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:121-153] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [INFERENCE: preserving bytes and observable outputs across a name-only move isolates path-resolution failures from later schema behavior]\n21: \n22: 4. **Checkpoint B must introduce compatibility in five ordered gates before deleting the bridge.** Gate B1 adds a pure normalizer that accepts the current v1 array and target v2 envelope and proves normalized acquisition-record equality over all 1,290 entries. Gate B2 adds the shared pure projector behind existing engine and DB call surfaces while continuing to publish/read `retrieval-manifest.json` as a bridge. Gate B3 proves projection parity record-for-record and DB parity for active/quarantined/tombstoned membership and representative ranked results; generation hashes may differ only where their versioned input contracts deliberately change. Gate B4 switches the harness writer to validated, canonical v2 and changes engine/DB source identity to the semantic hash, with purpose-specific generation-version bumps. Gate B5 deletes the bridge only after all readers use the projector and stale-cache tests pass. Rollback B restores the v1 writer/normalizer branch and bridge publication while the DB's independent current/rollback generation pointer remains available. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:392-435] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:434-637] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:623-753] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:121-153]\n23: \n24: 5. **Parity must compare semantics where identities intentionally change.** The v1-to-v2 gate compares normalized IDs, slugs, source fields, acquisition states, nullability, uniqueness, and 1,290-entry membership. Projection parity compares every enriched style record and deterministic ordering. DB parity compares active/inactive sets, row counts, aggregate content identities, and query results. The old retrieval `generationHash` and DB generation hash are not required to equal their v2 successors because source-hash and version contracts intentionally change; requiring byte/hash equality here would misclassify the planned migration as failure. Instead, each new hash must reproduce deterministically from its documented inputs, and rerunning the projector/indexer must be idempotent. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:552-637] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:187-206] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:740-753] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/canonical.mjs:21-69]\n25: \n26: 6. **Stale-cache proof needs four asymmetric mutations.** Reformatting the v2 manifest or permuting entries must preserve `sourceSemanticHash`; changing acquisition status/source data must change it; changing an artifact must preserve source identity but change that style's content hash and both purpose-specific generation identities; and poisoning only the bridge retrieval payload must be rejected by live projection/check logic even when its stored source/content hashes are unchanged. Before bridge deletion, also test missing bridge recovery and a stale bridge from the immediately previous source generation. These cases distinguish semantic source invalidation, artifact invalidation, and derived-cache corruption. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/canonical.mjs:21-69] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/check-stable.test.mjs:14-79] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:685-782] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/indexer.test.mjs:141-243]\n27: \n28: 7. **Bridge deletion and reference updates have explicit finish criteria, and documentation is status-classified.** Delete `retrieval-manifest.json` only when no runtime/code/test source loads it, the computed-path search and exact-token search are clean, engine and DB both consume the shared projector, missing/stale bridge tests have passed, a clean rebuild creates no bridge, and mutable docs no longer instruct operators to check/write it. Update current `README.md`, `SKILL.md`, feature-catalog entries, backend READMEs, manual-testing playbooks, active specs, and generated-reference source inputs in that order after code/tests stabilize. Preserve changelogs and completed-spec narratives verbatim; if current docs need to explain the migration, link to or name the historical path rather than rewriting historical statements. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/README.md:74] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:215-261] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/styles-library-utilization/retrieval-engine.md:42-54] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/manual-testing-playbook/styles-library-utilization/generation-guarded-hydration-mismatch.md:56] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n29: \n30: ## Questions Answered\n31: \n32: - **Answered:** Which imports, runtime paths, scripts, tests, docs, generated references, and indirect consumers change, and in what exact sequence? The direct inventory from iteration 1 is extended by computed `path.resolve`/`path.join` consumers, generated TypeScript output, confirmed command ownership, exact reference-update ordering, and mutable-versus-frozen documentation rules. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20]\n33: - **Answered:** What validation, rollback, and cutover plan proves no retrieval/generation breakage? Checkpoint A requires byte and observable parity for naming only; Checkpoint B requires v1/v2 normalized equivalence, projection/DB semantic parity, deterministic versioned hashes, stale-cache behavior, and bridge-deletion criteria, with independent reversals at each boundary. [INFERENCE: findings 3-7 define separately attributable proof and rollback obligations for both cutovers]\n34: \n35: ## Questions Remaining\n36: \n37: - No original key question remains unanswered. Iteration 5 must challenge every prior conclusion for internal inconsistency, untested assumptions, omitted consumers, rollback asymmetry, and conflicts between name-only parity and v2 semantic migration; it must not synthesize early. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-config.json:3-10]\n38: \n39: ## Ruled Out\n40: \n41: - Treating successful import resolution as sufficient name-only proof: computed manifest paths, fixture joins, operator docs, and retrieval/DB outputs can remain stale after imports resolve. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:47-68]\n42: - Deleting the retrieval bridge when the v2 writer lands: consumers must first move behind the shared projector and pass stale/missing bridge and DB parity gates. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:685-782] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:623-753]\n43: - Requiring old and new generation-hash equality across the schema cutover: versioned input contracts intentionally change, so reproducibility and semantic parity are the valid proofs. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:194-206] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:623-635]\n44: - Updating frozen history to make exact-token searches globally clean: the naming canon requires historical surfaces to retain shipped names, so searches must classify allowed historical matches. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n45: \n46: ## Dead Ends\n47: \n48: - A broad styles-tree documentation search for generic words such as `status` was dominated by the 1,290 style artifacts and did not improve backend command discovery. Restricting command discovery to package manifests, backend/mode READMEs, and exact CLI tokens is the productive implementation-time method. [INFERENCE: the broad scoped Grep returned style-content matches before backend README commands]\n49: - No architecture design was retried; permanent multi-writer and permanent retrieval-cache targets remain blocked by iteration 3. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:63-71]\n50: \n51: ## Sources Consulted\n52: \n53: - `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:24-45,77-94,169-195,197-313`\n54: - Detached config, state, strategy, registry, and iterations 1-3 under `research/lineages/sol-high-fast/`\n55: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:1-35`\n56: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66`\n57: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18`\n58: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17`\n59: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29`\n60: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32`\n61: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68`\n62: - Prior writer/projector/database/stale-cache sources cited in iterations 2-3.\n63: \n64: ## Assessment\n65: \n66: - New information ratio: **0.86** (5 of 7 findings are fully new command/cutover evidence and 2 partially extend prior sequencing and stale-cache findings: `(5 + 0.5 * 2) / 7 = 0.857`, rounded to 0.86).\n67: - Questions addressed: indirect/runtime-computed consumers; executable command ownership; name-only parity; v1/v2 normalization; projector/DB parity; stale-cache handling; rollback; bridge deletion; current-versus-frozen docs.\n68: - Questions answered: both remaining key questions; all 5 lineage questions are now evidence-backed, subject to iteration 5 adversarial review.\n69: - Status: **complete** for iteration 4; `stopPolicy=max-iterations` still requires iteration 5.\n70: - Edge cases: styles engine/database commands are explicitly inferred because no owning package script was found; generation hashes intentionally change at the schema boundary; frozen historical tokens remain allowed matches.\n71: \n72: ## Reflection\n73: \n74: - What worked and why: starting from observable parity and rollback checkpoints exposed command ownership, computed paths, and bridge-deletion prerequisites that a source-reference list alone could not prove.\n75: - What did not work and why: broad documentation grep under the style corpus was swamped by generated style prose; owner files and exact command tokens are the correct narrow scope.\n76: - What I would do differently: iteration 5 should test this plan backward from each rollback and deletion claim, looking especially for consumers that bypass the shared projector or artifacts that a clean rebuild does not reproduce.\n77: \n78: ## Recommended Next Focus\n79: \n80: Execute iteration 5 as a critical consistency/adversarial pass over iterations 1-4: verify the five-name map against every cited consumer class; challenge the one-writer v2 schema, semantic-hash definition, and purpose-specific generation identities; test whether Checkpoints A/B are independently reversible; look for omitted package hooks, generated files, environment-selected adapters, DB pointer behavior, and frozen-history misclassification; and report contradictions or remaining unknowns rather than synthesizing early.\n\n(End of file - total 80 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 4: Executable Cutover Validation, Rollback, and Indirect Consumers\n\n## Focus\n\nConvert the established name map and canonical-manifest architecture into an executable, two-checkpoint migration plan. This pass identifies runtime-computed paths, confirms the commands that repository package files and mode READMEs actually expose, separates inferred styles-backend commands from confirmed commands, and defines proof and rollback obligations for the name-only cutover and the later v1-to-v2 consolidation.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. Read the detached config, state, strategy, registry, and iterations 1-3; confirmed run 4, `progressiveSynthesis=false`, lineage-only writes, two remaining key questions, and the prohibition on combining naming and schema changes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-config.json:16-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:15-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:83-86]\n2. Searched the live `sk-design` surface for direct legacy tokens and runtime path construction (`import.meta.url`, `path.resolve`, `path.join`, and `new URL`) to distinguish static imports from computed consumers. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68]\n3. Located package manifests and executable test documentation. Only `design-md-generator/backend/package.json` exists under `sk-design`; it defines `typecheck`, `build`, and `test`, while the four mode-corpus READMEs expose direct `node --test` commands. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32]\n4. Reconciled the command/path evidence with prior writer, projector, stale-cache, database-generation, and frozen-history findings to derive exact ordering, checkpoint boundaries, and deletion criteria without running implementation or mutating tests. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:685-782] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:623-853] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n\n## Findings\n\n1. **The indirect consumer closure adds computed paths, fixture joins, and generated TypeScript output to the direct-reference inventory.** `study-prepare.ts` computes both the style-library CLI and retrieval-manifest locations with `path.resolve`, so changing imports alone would leave its runtime path stale. Mode-corpus fixtures construct `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` with `path.join`, so those strings must change even when their source imports resolve after the directory move. The backend build compiles TypeScript to `dist`; source is authoritative, then `npm run build` regenerates output, and generated output must not be hand-edited. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:14-20]\n\n2. **The executable baseline is a command matrix, not one package-level test command.** Repository-confirmed commands are `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`, and `npm test` from `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/`, plus `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, and `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs` from the repository root. No styles-level `package.json` was found, so `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/*.test.mjs` and the corresponding `_db` command are **inferred commands**, not repository-declared scripts; implementation must either confirm them by successful baseline execution or add an explicit documented runner before relying on them as gates. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32] [INFERENCE: the only package manifest found under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/**/package.json` is the backend package, while engine/database `.test.mjs` files are inventoried in iteration 1]\n\n3. **Checkpoint A is an atomic name-only dependency-closure cutover.** First record baseline command exits and stable observable fixtures: byte hashes and counts for both current manifests, representative legacy query/hydration results, database status/current-generation pointer, and the exact legacy-token inventory. Then move all five paths; update runtime imports and manifest constants first, computed `path.resolve`/`path.join` consumers second, test fixtures third, source scripts and generated-output inputs fourth, and mutable docs/operator commands last. Run the identical command matrix, require old/new manifest bytes to match across renamed paths, require retrieval/query/hydration and DB status snapshots to match, and require a scoped search to find no legacy tokens outside frozen history. Rollback A is one reversal of the five moves plus the same reference patch; schema and hash behavior remain untouched, so any behavioral delta is a naming regression. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:73-177] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:121-153] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [INFERENCE: preserving bytes and observable outputs across a name-only move isolates path-resolution failures from later schema behavior]","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-004.md","text":"# Iteration 4: Executable Cutover Validation, Rollback, and Indirect Consumers\n\n## Focus\n\nConvert the established name map and canonical-manifest architecture into an executable, two-checkpoint migration plan. This pass identifies runtime-computed paths, confirms the commands that repository package files and mode READMEs actually expose, separates inferred styles-backend commands from confirmed commands, and defines proof and rollback obligations for the name-only cutover and the later v1-to-v2 consolidation.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. Read the detached config, state, strategy, registry, and iterations 1-3; confirmed run 4, `progressiveSynthesis=false`, lineage-only writes, two remaining key questions, and the prohibition on combining naming and schema changes. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-config.json:16-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:15-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:83-86]\n2. Searched the live `sk-design` surface for direct legacy tokens and runtime path construction (`import.meta.url`, `path.resolve`, `path.join`, and `new URL`) to distinguish static imports from computed consumers. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68]\n3. Located package manifests and executable test documentation. Only `design-md-generator/backend/package.json` exists under `sk-design`; it defines `typecheck`, `build`, and `test`, while the four mode-corpus READMEs expose direct `node --test` commands. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32]\n4. Reconciled the command/path evidence with prior writer, projector, stale-cache, database-generation, and frozen-history findings to derive exact ordering, checkpoint boundaries, and deletion criteria without running implementation or mutating tests. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:685-782] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:623-853] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n\n## Findings\n\n1. **The indirect consumer closure adds computed paths, fixture joins, and generated TypeScript output to the direct-reference inventory.** `study-prepare.ts` computes both the style-library CLI and retrieval-manifest locations with `path.resolve`, so changing imports alone would leave its runtime path stale. Mode-corpus fixtures construct `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` with `path.join`, so those strings must change even when their source imports resolve after the directory move. The backend build compiles TypeScript to `dist`; source is authoritative, then `npm run build` regenerates output, and generated output must not be hand-edited. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:14-20]\n\n2. **The executable baseline is a command matrix, not one package-level test command.** Repository-confirmed commands are `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`, and `npm test` from `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/`, plus `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, and `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs` from the repository root. No styles-level `package.json` was found, so `node --test .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/*.test.mjs` and the corresponding `_db` command are **inferred commands**, not repository-declared scripts; implementation must either confirm them by successful baseline execution or add an explicit documented runner before relying on them as gates. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32] [INFERENCE: the only package manifest found under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/**/package.json` is the backend package, while engine/database `.test.mjs` files are inventoried in iteration 1]\n\n3. **Checkpoint A is an atomic name-only dependency-closure cutover.** First record baseline command exits and stable observable fixtures: byte hashes and counts for both current manifests, representative legacy query/hydration results, database status/current-generation pointer, and the exact legacy-token inventory. Then move all five paths; update runtime imports and manifest constants first, computed `path.resolve`/`path.join` consumers second, test fixtures third, source scripts and generated-output inputs fourth, and mutable docs/operator commands last. Run the identical command matrix, require old/new manifest bytes to match across renamed paths, require retrieval/query/hydration and DB status snapshots to match, and require a scoped search to find no legacy tokens outside frozen history. Rollback A is one reversal of the five moves plus the same reference patch; schema and hash behavior remain untouched, so any behavioral delta is a naming regression. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:73-177] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:121-153] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [INFERENCE: preserving bytes and observable outputs across a name-only move isolates path-resolution failures from later schema behavior]\n\n4. **Checkpoint B must introduce compatibility in five ordered gates before deleting the bridge.** Gate B1 adds a pure normalizer that accepts the current v1 array and target v2 envelope and proves normalized acquisition-record equality over all 1,290 entries. Gate B2 adds the shared pure projector behind existing engine and DB call surfaces while continuing to publish/read `retrieval-manifest.json` as a bridge. Gate B3 proves projection parity record-for-record and DB parity for active/quarantined/tombstoned membership and representative ranked results; generation hashes may differ only where their versioned input contracts deliberately change. Gate B4 switches the harness writer to validated, canonical v2 and changes engine/DB source identity to the semantic hash, with purpose-specific generation-version bumps. Gate B5 deletes the bridge only after all readers use the projector and stale-cache tests pass. Rollback B restores the v1 writer/normalizer branch and bridge publication while the DB's independent current/rollback generation pointer remains available. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:392-435] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:434-637] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:623-753] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:121-153]\n\n5. **Parity must compare semantics where identities intentionally change.** The v1-to-v2 gate compares normalized IDs, slugs, source fields, acquisition states, nullability, uniqueness, and 1,290-entry membership. Projection parity compares every enriched style record and deterministic ordering. DB parity compares active/inactive sets, row counts, aggregate content identities, and query results. The old retrieval `generationHash` and DB generation hash are not required to equal their v2 successors because source-hash and version contracts intentionally change; requiring byte/hash equality here would misclassify the planned migration as failure. Instead, each new hash must reproduce deterministically from its documented inputs, and rerunning the projector/indexer must be idempotent. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:552-637] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:187-206] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:740-753] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/canonical.mjs:21-69]\n\n6. **Stale-cache proof needs four asymmetric mutations.** Reformatting the v2 manifest or permuting entries must preserve `sourceSemanticHash`; changing acquisition status/source data must change it; changing an artifact must preserve source identity but change that style's content hash and both purpose-specific generation identities; and poisoning only the bridge retrieval payload must be rejected by live projection/check logic even when its stored source/content hashes are unchanged. Before bridge deletion, also test missing bridge recovery and a stale bridge from the immediately previous source generation. These cases distinguish semantic source invalidation, artifact invalidation, and derived-cache corruption. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/canonical.mjs:21-69] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/check-stable.test.mjs:14-79] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:685-782] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/indexer.test.mjs:141-243]\n\n7. **Bridge deletion and reference updates have explicit finish criteria, and documentation is status-classified.** Delete `retrieval-manifest.json` only when no runtime/code/test source loads it, the computed-path search and exact-token search are clean, engine and DB both consume the shared projector, missing/stale bridge tests have passed, a clean rebuild creates no bridge, and mutable docs no longer instruct operators to check/write it. Update current `README.md`, `SKILL.md`, feature-catalog entries, backend READMEs, manual-testing playbooks, active specs, and generated-reference source inputs in that order after code/tests stabilize. Preserve changelogs and completed-spec narratives verbatim; if current docs need to explain the migration, link to or name the historical path rather than rewriting historical statements. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/README.md:74] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:215-261] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/styles-library-utilization/retrieval-engine.md:42-54] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/manual-testing-playbook/styles-library-utilization/generation-guarded-hydration-mismatch.md:56] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n\n## Questions Answered\n\n- **Answered:** Which imports, runtime paths, scripts, tests, docs, generated references, and indirect consumers change, and in what exact sequence? The direct inventory from iteration 1 is extended by computed `path.resolve`/`path.join` consumers, generated TypeScript output, confirmed command ownership, exact reference-update ordering, and mutable-versus-frozen documentation rules. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20]\n- **Answered:** What validation, rollback, and cutover plan proves no retrieval/generation breakage? Checkpoint A requires byte and observable parity for naming only; Checkpoint B requires v1/v2 normalized equivalence, projection/DB semantic parity, deterministic versioned hashes, stale-cache behavior, and bridge-deletion criteria, with independent reversals at each boundary. [INFERENCE: findings 3-7 define separately attributable proof and rollback obligations for both cutovers]\n\n## Questions Remaining\n\n- No original key question remains unanswered. Iteration 5 must challenge every prior conclusion for internal inconsistency, untested assumptions, omitted consumers, rollback asymmetry, and conflicts between name-only parity and v2 semantic migration; it must not synthesize early. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-config.json:3-10]\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Treating successful import resolution as sufficient name-only proof: computed manifest paths, fixture joins, operator docs, and retrieval/DB outputs can remain stale after imports resolve. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:47-68]\n- Deleting the retrieval bridge when the v2 writer lands: consumers must first move behind the shared projector and pass stale/missing bridge and DB parity gates. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:685-782] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:623-753]\n- Requiring old and new generation-hash equality across the schema cutover: versioned input contracts intentionally change, so reproducibility and semantic parity are the valid proofs. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:194-206] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:623-635]\n- Updating frozen history to make exact-token searches globally clean: the naming canon requires historical surfaces to retain shipped names, so searches must classify allowed historical matches. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:56]\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- A broad styles-tree documentation search for generic words such as `status` was dominated by the 1,290 style artifacts and did not improve backend command discovery. Restricting command discovery to package manifests, backend/mode READMEs, and exact CLI tokens is the productive implementation-time method. [INFERENCE: the broad scoped Grep returned style-content matches before backend README commands]\n- No architecture design was retried; permanent multi-writer and permanent retrieval-cache targets remain blocked by iteration 3. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md:63-71]\n\n## Sources Consulted\n\n- `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:24-45,77-94,169-195,197-313`\n- Detached config, state, strategy, registry, and iterations 1-3 under `research/lineages/sol-high-fast/`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:1-35`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-66`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/README.md:18`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/README.md:17`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/README.md:29`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/README.md:32`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/motion-evidence.test.mjs:16-68`\n- Prior writer/projector/database/stale-cache sources cited in iterations 2-3.\n\n## Assessment\n\n- New information ratio: **0.86** (5 of 7 findings are fully new command/cutover evidence and 2 partially extend prior sequencing and stale-cache findings: `(5 + 0.5 * 2) / 7 = 0.857`, rounded to 0.86).\n- Questions addressed: indirect/runtime-computed consumers; executable command ownership; name-only parity; v1/v2 normalization; projector/DB parity; stale-cache handling; rollback; bridge deletion; current-versus-frozen docs.\n- Questions answered: both remaining key questions; all 5 lineage questions are now evidence-backed, subject to iteration 5 adversarial review.\n- Status: **complete** for iteration 4; `stopPolicy=max-iterations` still requires iteration 5.\n- Edge cases: styles engine/database commands are explicitly inferred because no owning package script was found; generation hashes intentionally change at the schema boundary; frozen historical tokens remain allowed matches.\n\n## Reflection\n\n- What worked and why: starting from observable parity and rollback checkpoints exposed command ownership, computed paths, and bridge-deletion prerequisites that a source-reference list alone could not prove.\n- What did not work and why: broad documentation grep under the style corpus was swamped by generated style prose; owner files and exact command tokens are the correct narrow scope.\n- What I would do differently: iteration 5 should test this plan backward from each rollback and deletion claim, looking especially for consumers that bypass the shared projector or artifacts that a clean rebuild does not reproduce.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n\nExecute iteration 5 as a critical consistency/adversarial pass over iterations 1-4: verify the five-name map against every cited consumer class; challenge the one-writer v2 schema, semantic-hash definition, and purpose-specific generation identities; test whether Checkpoints A/B are independently reversible; look for omitted package hooks, generated files, environment-selected adapters, DB pointer behavior, and frozen-history misclassification; and report contradictions or remaining unknowns rather than synthesizing early.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":80,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/002-naming-manifests/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-004.md","time":{"start":1784621825329,"end":1784621825335}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e089a0d6ae91f7d016a5f2b011af48191918d8a55b9fc37d8"}},"id":"prt_f83bffcba0017Cqh3EC1u34Q1f","sessionID":"ses_07c62e1e5ffemFsnADH4fVqMT5","messageID":"msg_f83bfdbee001b3UvsdJBN4XK3X"}}
